This coming weekend, Global Citizen will be hosting the One World: Together At Home show. The concert is aimed at raising funds in support of healthcare workers fighting Covid-19 around the world, where the money from the concert will be given to health workers and charities that provide food, shelter and healthcare. READ: TJOVITJO NOW ON NETFLIX The international organisation that previously hosted the Global Citizen Festival Mandela 100 last year in Mzansi recently shared some good news on their social media pages. It announced that Black Coffee, Cassper Nyovest and Sho Madjozi will be joining the list of international acts for their concert. Local artist and brand Global Citizen brand ambassador Nomzamo Mbatha will be joining Lady Gaga, Andrea Bocelli, Burna Boy, Chris Martin, Danai Gurira, David Beckham, Elton John, Idris and Sabrina Elba, John Legend, Kerry Washington, Lewis Hamilton, Lizzo, Samuel L Jackson and Stevie Wonder. ALSO READ: SOMIZI GRANTED BAIL FOR LOCKDOWN COMMENT The concert will air this Saturday, 18 April on online platforms. Before the Coronavirus worsened globally,  the event was on in the United States for almost three weeks. SEE POST BELOW:    